  "texts": [
    "During this process, coefficients from mapping functions vary; first, they can be initialized to average expected human values.",
    "Then, they can be optimized through algorithms such as Least Squares to minimize the distance between the calibration targets and calculated gaze locations (Chugh 2020; Lu et al. 2020).",
    "Some of the calibration measurements may be discarded whether they are considered outliers through statistical analysis, thus avoiding inaccurately estimating the model coefficients (Chugh 2020).",
    "Once calibrated, images acquired either from RGB or IR cameras, as well as numerical data from headset sensors must be processed to estimate the origin of the gaze vector.",
    "The most frequent pipelines in computer vision for estimating the gaze vector are feature-based and model-based methods, besides AI ones."
